<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Ssgt:
[B]Heres my 2 cps worth on where to fight:

From 1 - 5 stay in everfrost killing the gobs and gnoll pups and the like. But make sure you try to exclusively kill polar bear cubs from 3 - 5. This will help you get basically free patchwork armor.

For 5 - 7 Go to BB dont go anywhere that leads down, LOL the 4 gnolls on the everfrost ramp are really good to take out.

For 8 - 10 Group with 1 or 2 others and take out leopards giant whooly spiders and the orcs. Good xp and fair loot. Also you can try the lower levels of bb but you will get sick of trains soon. the giant snakes are good to kill in bb as well and for a lvl 8 or 9 characyer the loot is great. at these lvls save up for a Bloodforge Hammer. Make sure you have one by 10th.

For 10 - 15 Eruds crossing Beast area ive ever seen for loot espeacially. go get those whisps. 


Thats where i am at now. A few more Greater Light Stones for my smithing skill and ill be off to oasis i imagine. I hope this helps.


Saensatia Barbarian Shaman of the 15th circle[/B][/QUOTE]

