<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Saldeira</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I'm so fed up with BlackBurrow but it seems the only place to fight at level 6.  Can someone suggest somewhere else?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Beowulfe Grendelbane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">From level 6 - 15 I fought on the tundra. At level 6 it was Wolves and Ice Goblin Scouts, then on to Polar Bears, Skellies, Giant Spiders, Cats and Orc Troopers; stick close to One guard. <P>Once you hit level 9 or so, find a group and head out to North or South Tower and look for higher level Troopers, etc, and start to fight the weaker Orc Mouties and Mammoth Calves. <P>Around Level 11 you can start to kill Orc Shamen and Ice Boned Skellies. Calves, Mounties, Ice Bones and Shamen can take you right up to 15 or 16 if you so desire (actually Shamen can take you beyond even that, but it would be slow going).<P>I truly hated trying to level in BB myself, but found the Tundra to be a lot more fun, especially with a good group. I'll be 15 today and in search of greener pastures, but I'll always be happy to return to our snowy home (In my 20's it's Mammas and Permafrost    <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/wink.gif">).<P>Hope that helped.<P>------------------<BR>Beowulfe (soon to be Grendelbane)<BR>Barbarian Shaman of the 14th Totem<BR>Excellent Smith trained exclusively in Halas<BR>Quellious Server<P>[This message has been edited by Beowulfe Grendelbane (edited 11-27-1999).]<p>[This message has been edited by Beowulfe Grendelbane (edited 11-27-1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Askaria</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">You might also want to try the Karanas.  Start in West Karana, then at about 9 you can move to North Karana.  Later you will be able to move to East and South.<P>Another place you might want to consider is North Ro.  After a while you will be able to go to Oasis and fight.<P>Best of luck to you.<P>Askaria Gunnarson<BR>Karana Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ssgt</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Heres my 2 cps worth on where to fight:<P>From 1 - 5 stay in everfrost killing the gobs and gnoll pups and the like. But make sure you try to exclusively kill polar bear cubs from 3 - 5. This will help you get basically free patchwork armor.<P>For 5 - 7 Go to BB dont go anywhere that leads down, LOL the 4 gnolls on the everfrost ramp are really good to take out.<P>For 8 - 10 Group with 1 or 2 others and take out leopards giant whooly spiders and the orcs. Good xp and fair loot. Also you can try the lower levels of bb but you will get sick of trains soon. the giant snakes are good to kill in bb as well and for a lvl 8 or 9 characyer the loot is great. at these lvls save up for a Bloodforge Hammer. Make sure you have one by 10th.<P>For 10 - 15 Eruds crossing Beast area ive ever seen for loot espeacially. go get those whisps. <P><BR>Thats where i am at now. A few more Greater Light Stones for my smithing skill and ill be off to oasis i imagine. I hope this helps.<P><BR>Saensatia Barbarian Shaman of the 15th circle</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
